paper_metadata.title: MAIN TEXT
paper_metadata.extraction_summary: The paper discusses the presence of transthyretin (TTR) amyloid deposits in patients with lumbar spinal stenosis, suggesting a potential link to senile systemic amyloidosis (SSA). However, no specific genetic variants in the TTR gene are mentioned.

tables_processed.table_caption: Total material analyzed for presence of amyloid from patients with lumbar spinal stenosis.
Amyloid-containing materials with or without reactivity with an anti TTR antibody at immunohistochemistry.

challenges: No specific genetic variants in the TTR gene were mentioned in the paper.
extraction_metadata.notes: The paper focuses on the presence of TTR amyloid deposits in spinal stenosis but does not provide specific genetic variant data for TTR.
